commitResults.messageBody:
Add the ability to store whatever text entered by the user and
display them back to the user when requested.

Add the ability to mark tasks as done. Optionally, add the ability to
change the status back to not done.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add Deadline.java, Event.java and Todo.java as well as update Duke.java
commitResults.messageBody:
Add support for tracking three types of tasks:
-Todos: tasks without any date/time attached to it
-Deadlines: tasks that need to be done before a specific date/time
-Events: tasks that start at a specific time and ends at a specific time

commitResults.messageTitle: Add input.txt and EXPECTED.TXT as well as update Duke.java
commitResults.messageBody:
Use the input/output redirection technique to semi-automate the testing
of Duke.
Teach Duke to deal with errors such as incorrect inputs entered by user.
Add support for deleting tasks from the list.

Save the tasks in the hard disk automatically whenever the task list
changes. Load the data from the hard disk when Duke starts up.

Store deadline dates as a java.time.LocalDate in task objects. Accept
dates in a format such as yyyy-mm-dd format (e.g., 2019-10-15) and print
in a different format such as MMM dd yyyy e.g., (Oct 15 2019).
